extends ../index

block append pageVariables
    - var moduleTitle = "Getting started"

block content

    .o-container-vertical
        h1.c-d-h1 Getting started

        .o-grid
            .o-grid-col-bp3-3
                .u-spacer-bottom
                    .u-spacer-right-bp3
                        ul.c-side-menu
                            li.c-side-menu__item(class=pathname.match(/development\/getting-started/) ? "c-side-menu__item--active" : "")
                                a.c-side-menu__link(href="/development/getting-started.html") Getting started

                            li.c-side-menu__item(class=pathname.match(/development\/example-pages/) ? "c-side-menu__item--active" : "")
                                a.c-side-menu__link(href="/development/example-pages.html") Example pages

                            li.c-side-menu__item(class=pathname.match(/development\/package/) ? "c-side-menu__item--active" : "")
                                a.c-side-menu__link(href="/development/package-and-repo-links.html") Package and repo links

            .o-grid-col-bp3-9
                block subContent

                    .c-display

                        h2 Usage

                        p Please link to the stylesheet in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> of your application:

                        pre
                            code &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://design.smart.coop/css/main.css"&gt;

                        p Go to the <a href="https://design.smart.coop/development/component-documentation.html">component documentation</a>, and find the component you need.

                        p Copy paste the HTML (or Pug if you are using this template language), and you are on your way to create an app.

                        hr.c-hr

                        h2 Using Pug

                        p If you use the Pug templating language in your own project, you will need to include the mixins in your global namespace in your app. You can find the mixins <a href="https://github.com/smartcoop/design/tree/main/content/templates/_mixins">here</a>. There is a very specific icon mixin which you can find <a href="https://github.com/smartcoop/design/blob/main/core/templates/mixins/icon.pug">here</a>.

                        hr.c-hr

                        h2 Codepen

                        p You can fork this <a href="https://codepen.io/wolfr/pen/JjJZqoq">pen</a> to get started, it contains the right settings.
